## Question 2(c): External CSS

### (i) Change all heading 2 and heading 4 to italic style with a font size of 13pt. (3 marks)

**Answer (External CSS):**

```css
h2, h4 {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 13pt;
}
```

**Explanation:**

* `h2, h4` selects both heading elements.
* `font-style: italic` sets italic text.
* `font-size: 13pt` sets the font size as specified.

---

### (ii) Set the footer element to display text with a line height of 9em, horizontally centred, and a letter spacing of 0.7em. (4 marks)

**Answer (External CSS):**

```css
footer {
    line-height: 9em;
    text-align: center;
    letter-spacing: 0.7em;
}
```

**Explanation:**

* `line-height` controls vertical spacing between lines.
* `text-align: center` centres text horizontally.
* `letter-spacing` controls spacing between characters.

---

## Question 2(b): HTML Form Input Controls

### Given Figure 2, write the necessary HTML code to place the specified input controls. (Total: 10 marks)

---

### (i) Set the Order ID textbox with the name and id as `ordID` and the placeholder text as *Enter your ID*. (3 marks)

**Answer (HTML):**

```html
<label for="ordID">Order ID:</label>
<input type="text" name="ordID" id="ordID" placeholder="Enter your ID">
```

**Explanation:**

* `type="text"` creates a textbox.
* `name` and `id` are set to `ordID` as required.
* `placeholder` displays hint text inside the textbox.

---

### (ii) Set the Time picker with the name and id as `ordTime` to display 10:00 AM by default, with an acceptable range between 10:00 and 21:00. (4 marks)

**Answer (HTML):**

```html
<label for="ordTime">Time:</label>
<input type="time"
       name="ordTime"
       id="ordTime"
       value="10:00"
       min="10:00"
       max="21:00">
```

**Explanation:**

* `type="time"` creates a time picker input.
* `value="10:00"` sets the default time (24-hour format).
* `min` and `max` restrict the allowed time range.

---

### (iii) Set the Sample Picture file picker with the name and id as `ordFile` allowing only JPG and PNG files. (3 marks)

**Answer (HTML):**

```html
<label for="ordFile">Sample Picture:</label>
<input type="file"
       name="ordFile"
       id="ordFile"
       accept=".jpg,.png">
```

**Explanation:**

* `type="file"` allows file upload.
* `accept` restricts the file types to JPG and PNG.

---

### Combined Safe Examination Answer

```html
<form>

  <label for="ordID">Order ID:</label>
  <input type="text" name="ordID" id="ordID" placeholder="Enter your ID">
  <br><br>

  <label for="ordTime">Time:</label>
  <input type="time"
         name="ordTime"
         id="ordTime"
         value="10:00"
         min="10:00"
         max="21:00">
  <br><br>

  <label for="ordFile">Sample Picture:</label>
  <input type="file"
         name="ordFile"
         id="ordFile"
         accept=".jpg,.png">

</form>
```

